page.title: 17WILDLIFE,FLOWERS,INSECTS,
page.content: THESE ASPECTS OF THE COUNTRYSIDE WERE SEEN IN THE AREA DURING THE TIME OF STUDY: {FLOWERS_}MEADOW SWEET BEAKED PARSLEY HAREBELL BUTTERCUP {WILDLIFE}_THERE IS A VARIETY OF WILDLIFE IN THIS AREA BUT AS MOST OF THE LAND IS FARMLAND THE FARMERS HAVE PRIORITY OVER THE ANIMALS AS THEY CAN BE PESTS EG. RABBITS EAT CROPS, FOXES EAT STOCK LIKE CHICKENS,PHEASANTS EAT SEEDS ETC.ANIMALS SEEN ARE-FOXES BADGERS RABBITS AND HARES AND THERE ARE MANY TYPES OF BIRD SEEN. {INSECTS}SEEN INCLUDE WASPS GNATS FLIES BEES WATER BEETLES. MANY OTHERS CAN BE SEEN IN THE AREA.
